The balance of certain types of agricultural products and foodstuffs is calculated according to the following scheme: the basis for determining the food resources of certain types of agricultural products and foodstuffs is the balance method.
The balance scheme is generally expressed by the following formula:
Zn + Pr + I = PP + E + P + Zk + FP 
where: Zn – stocks at the beginning of the year;
CC – stocks at the end of the year;
Pr – production volume;
And – import;
PP – the volume of production consumption;
E – export; 
P – losses;
FP is a fund for personal consumption by the population.
